---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Callout from '../../components/Callout.astro';

const article = { author: "Maine Dispensary Guide Editorial Team", publishDate: "2026-01-21", modifiedDate: "2026-03-22", section: "Operations & Technology" };
---

<Layout 
  title="Maine Dispensary Packaging & Labeling | Maine Dispensary Guide" 
  description="In-depth technical resource for Maine Dispensary Packaging & Labeling within the Maine cannabis industry. Professional 2026 guidance on licensing, compliance, and strategic market positioning."
  heroImage="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1589939705384-5185137a7f0f?auto=format&fit=crop&q=80&w=1200&h=400"
  article={article}
>
  <article>
    <div class="article-header">
      <h1>Packaging & Labeling Requirements</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Understanding Maine's cannabis <a href="/guides/maine-dispensary-packaging/">packaging</a> and labeling regulations</p>
    </div>

    <section>
      <h2>Overview</h2>
      <p>Maine has strict packaging and labeling requirements designed to protect consumers, prevent accidental ingestion, and ensure product safety. Compliance is mandatory and enforced by the Maine Office of Cannabis Policy.</p>
    </section>

    <Callout title="The Art of the Reveal" type="tip">
      Packaging is your chance to make a first impression. While the rules are strict, finding creative ways to tell your brand story through compliant, high-quality materials is part of the fun. It's the physical representation of the care and quality you put into your products.
    </Callout>

    <section>
      <h2>Packaging Requirements</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Child-resistant packaging mandatory for all products</li>
        <li>Opaque packaging required for all exit transactions</li>
        <li>THC content clearly labeled per serving and per package</li>
        <li>Producer name, batch number, and harvest date displayed</li>
        <li>Laboratory testing required before sale</li>
        <li>Source from approved suppliers</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="further-reading">
      <h2>Further Reading</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://www.maine.gov/dafs/ocp/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Maine Office of Cannabis Policy (OCP)</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://www.maine.gov/dafs/ocp/adult-use/packaging-labeling" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">OCP Packaging & Labeling Guide</a></li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="disclaimer">
      <p><em>Requirements subject to change. Verify current Maine OCP requirements.</em></p>
    </section>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  article { max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .article-header { margin-bottom: 2rem; padding-bottom: 1.5rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  .subtitle { font-size: 1.25rem; color: var(--color-text-light); }
  section { margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  section h2, section h3 { margin-top: 1.5rem; }
  section h2:first-child { margin-top: 0; }
  section h3 { font-size: 1.1rem; }
  ul { padding-left: 1.5rem; }
  li { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .disclaimer { background: #fff3cd; border: 1px solid #ffc107; padding: 1rem; border-radius: 0.5rem; font-size: 0.875rem; }
  .further-reading { background: rgba(88, 129, 87, 0.05); padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: 1rem; margin-top: 3rem; }
  .further-reading h2 { margin-top: 0; font-size: 1.25rem; }
</style>
